winning_structure.comment: This message is deprecated in protocol versions greater than 23.01. Use UBX-CFG-VALSET, UBX-CFG-VALGET, UBX-CFG-VALDEL instead. This message configures the SBAS receiver subsystem (i.e. WAAS, EGNOS, MSAS). See SBAS configuration settings description in the integration manual for a detailed description of how these settings affect receiver operation.

bit_fields.name: enabled
bit_fields.description: SBAS enabled (1) / disabled (0) This field is deprecated; use UBX-CFG-GNSS to enable/disable SBAS operation

bit_fields.name: test
bit_fields.description: SBAS testbed: Use data anyhow (1)/Ignore data when in test mode (SBAS msg 0)

bit_fields.name: range
bit_fields.description: Use SBAS GEOs as a ranging source (for navigation)

bit_fields.name: integrity
bit_fields.description: Use SBAS integrity information. If enabled, the receiver will only use GPS satellites for which integrity information is available.

payload_fields.name: maxSBAS
payload_fields.description: Maximum number of SBAS prioritized tracking channels (valid range: 0-3) to use (obsolete and superseded by UBX-CFG-GNSS for protocol versions 14.00+).

payload_fields.name: scanmode1
payload_fields.description: Which SBAS PRN numbers to search for (bitmask). If all bits are set to zero, auto-scan (i.e. all valid PRNs) are searched. Every bit corresponds to a PRN number.
